SIMPLE: fineness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fineness
<hw>Fine"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Fine</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or condition of being
fine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Freedom from foreign matter or alloy; clearness;
purity; <as>as, the <ex>fineness</ex> of liquor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>fineness</qex> of the gold, and chargeful fashion.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The proportion of pure silver or gold in jewelry,
bullion, or coins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The fineness of United States coin is nine tenths, that
of English gold coin is eleven twelfths, and that of English silver coin
is ⟦frac925x1000⟧.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Keenness or sharpness; <as>as, the <ex>fineness</ex>
of a needle's point, or of the edge of a blade</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Finer</ent>⟦br⟧
